node.contents: 1) You may add @SerializedName name to your Mod class and other json response related classes.

astNode.text: 1) You may add @SerializedName name to your Mod class and other json response related classes.

node.contents: 2) You may say proguard to not obfuscate a Java model if it is in a specific package which is related with your json response. As I see from your error log; your Mod class is obfuscated and its name became a. So; you can add something like below to the proguard.cfg file:

astNode.text: 2) You may say proguard to not obfuscate a Java model if it is in a specific package which is related with your json response. As I see from your error log; your Mod class is obfuscated and its name became a. So; you can add something like below to the proguard.cfg file:

elements.contents: # Gson uses generic type information stored in a class file when working with fields. # removes such information by default, so configure it to keep all of it. -keepattributes Signature # Gson specific classes -keep class sun.misc.Unsafe { *; } # Application classes that will be serialized/deserialized over Gson -keep class ru.ensemplix.** { *; }
